{"nodes":[{"pos":[12,49],"content":"Compiler Error C2297 | Microsoft Docs","needQuote":false,"needEscape":true,"nodes":[{"content":"Compiler Error C2297 | Microsoft Docs","pos":[0,37]}]},{"content":"Compiler Error C2297","pos":[597,617]},{"content":"'operator' : bad right operand","pos":[618,648]},{"pos":[655,705],"content":"The right operand used with <ph id=\"ph1\">`operator`</ph> is invalid.","source":"The right operand used with `operator` is invalid."},{"content":"For example, the compiler may see a declaration where you intended a function call.","pos":[712,795]},{"content":"The following sample generates C2297:","pos":[802,839]}],"content":"---\ntitle: \"Compiler Error C2297 | Microsoft Docs\"\nms.custom: \"\"\nms.date: \"11/04/2016\"\nms.reviewer: \"\"\nms.suite: \"\"\nms.technology: \n  - \"devlang-cpp\"\nms.tgt_pltfrm: \"\"\nms.topic: \"error-reference\"\nf1_keywords: \n  - \"C2297\"\ndev_langs: \n  - \"C++\"\nhelpviewer_keywords: \n  - \"C2297\"\nms.assetid: 65849fe5-17e1-4b7e-b50c-f508b05ddaa4\ncaps.latest.revision: 8\nauthor: \"corob-msft\"\nms.author: \"corob\"\nmanager: \"ghogen\"\ntranslation.priority.ht: \n  - \"cs-cz\"\n  - \"de-de\"\n  - \"es-es\"\n  - \"fr-fr\"\n  - \"it-it\"\n  - \"ja-jp\"\n  - \"ko-kr\"\n  - \"pl-pl\"\n  - \"pt-br\"\n  - \"ru-ru\"\n  - \"tr-tr\"\n  - \"zh-cn\"\n  - \"zh-tw\"\n---\n# Compiler Error C2297\n'operator' : bad right operand  \n  \n The right operand used with `operator` is invalid.  \n  \n For example, the compiler may see a declaration where you intended a function call.  \n  \n The following sample generates C2297:  \n  \n```  \n// C2297.cpp  \nstruct MyStruct {  \n   struct Help {  \n      Help(float f) : m_f(f) {}  \n      float m_f;  \n   };  \n  \n   MyStruct(const Help &h) : m_f(h.m_f) {}  \n  \n   MyStruct(float f) : m_f(f) {}  \n  \n   MyStruct operator*(const MyStruct &f1) const {   \n      return MyStruct(m_f * f1.m_f);  \n   }  \n  \nprivate:  \n   float m_f;  \n};  \n  \nint main() {  \n   float f1 = 1.0f;  \n  \n   MyStruct m_MyStruct1 ( MyStruct::Help( f1 ) );  \n   // try the following line instead  \n   // MyStruct m_MyStruct1 = MyStruct::Help( f1 );  \n  \n   MyStruct m_MyStruct2 ( MyStruct::Help( f1 ) );  \n   // try the following line instead  \n   // MyStruct m_MyStruct2 = MyStruct::Help( f1 );  \n  \n   MyStruct m_MyStruct3 = m_MyStruct1 * m_MyStruct2;   // C2297  \n}  \n```"}